{
  "texts": [
    "Without such intentionality-for example, if employees rush to apply the knowledge without taking the time to carefully evaluate it-the knowledge contained in GenAI could be misapplied.",
    "Further, the time saved from an extensive search may be partially offset by the need to carefully evaluate the veracity and applicability of the knowledge.",
    "Likewise, employees may spend time asking GenAI irrelevant questions, much as employees spent time surfing the web during work hours when the internet first appeared, reducing the productivity gains of the internet.",
    "Second, applying the knowledge generated by GenAI tools may yield intellectual property risks that can take two forms: (1) leaking the firm's intellectual, confidential, and protected information by including it in GenAI prompts and queries, and (2) the unauthorized access and use of information protected by copyright, intellectual property, and privacy laws, which could lead to legal challenges.",
    "For instance, Getty Images, a photography agency, sued Stability AI (a GenAI model vendor) for using Getty's copyrighted material without permission (Brittain, 2023)."
  ]
}